{
  "local_port": 35384,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "I'm doing my first pyromancer build in Dark Souls 3. What stats do I need to build on to be most effective?",
  "response": "Creating an effective Pyromancer build in **Dark Souls 3** involves carefully allocating your character's stats to maximize your pyromancy spells while maintaining survivability and versatility in combat. Below is a comprehensive guide to help you set up a robust Pyromancer build.\n\n## **1. Starting Class and Gift**\n\n- **Starting Class:** **Pyromancer** is the best starting class for this build as it begins with balanced stats in Intelligence and Faith, essential for pyromancy.\n- **Starting Gift:** The **Young Dragon Ring** can slightly boost pyromancy damage, but it's optional. Alternatively, the **Fire Gem** or **Life Ring** can also be beneficial depending on your initial preference.\n\n## **2. Core Stats to Focus On**\n\n### **a. Intelligence (INT)**\n- **Role:** Primary stat for scaling pyromancy damage.\n- **Recommendation:** Aim for at least **35-50**. Each pyromancy spell scales with Intelligence, so higher INT directly increases your spell damage.\n\n### **b. Faith (FTH)**\n- **Role:** Secondary stat that also influences pyromancy scaling.\n- **Recommendation:** Aim for **35-50**. Balancing Faith with Intelligence ensures that your pyromancies scale well and deal maximum damage.\n\n### **c. Attunement (ATT)**\n- **Role:** Increases the number of attunement slots (spell slots) and reduces casting time.\n- **Recommendation:** Aim for **20-25** early on, then gradually increase to **30-40** as you progress. More attunement slots allow you to equip more pyromancy spells.\n\n### **d. Vigor (VIG)**\n- **Role:** Determines your health pool.\n- **Recommendation:** Aim for **25-40**. A higher Vigor ensures you can survive longer in melee and against strong enemies.\n\n### **e. Endurance (END)**\n- **Role:** Affects stamina and equip load.\n- **Recommendation:** Aim for **20-30**. Enough to allow for rolling and wielding necessary gear without being over-encumbered.\n\n## **3. Supporting Stats**\n\n### **a. Dexterity (DEX) and Strength (STR)**\n- **Role:** Not a focus, but some weapons scaling may require minimal investment.\n- **Recommendation:** Keep **DEX** and **STR** around **12-16**, just enough to meet weapon requirements if you choose to wield specific weapons.\n\n### **b. Vitality (VIT)**\n- **Role:** Increases equip load.\n- **Recommendation:** Typically, **15-20** to allow for medium armor without restricting movement.\n\n## **4. Equipment Recommendations**\n\n### **a. Pyromancy Flame**\n- **Upgrade Path:** Always upgrade your Pyromancy Flame using **Pyromancy Flame Ashes** to increase spell damage.\n- **Types:** Choose a flame type based on your preferred playstyle (e.g., **Black Flame**, **Great Chaos Fire Orb**).\n\n### **b. Rings**\n- **Great Swamp Ring** or **Bellowing Dragoncrest Ring:** Boost pyromancy damage.\n- **Young Dragon Ring:** Increase pyromancy damage but may reduce health slightly.\n- **Scholar Ring:** Increase Attunement.\n\n### **c. Armor**\n- **Light to Medium Armor:** Ensures you have sufficient mobility to cast spells effectively and dodge attacks.\n\n## **5. Spell Selection**\n\n- **Early Game:** Focus on basic pyromancies like **Fireball** and **Great Combustion**.\n- **Mid to Late Game:** Unlock more potent spells like **Great Chaos Fireball**, **Iron Flesh**, and utility spells like **Hidden Chaos**.\n\n## **6. Gameplay Tips**\n\n- **Manage FP:** Keep an eye on your Focus Points (FP) when casting spells. Allocate enough Attunement slots to include crucial pyromancies without running out of slots for healing items like **Crimson Flasks**.\n- **Balance Offense and Defense:** While focusing on spells, don\u2019t neglect your defensive capabilities. Equip armor that provides a good balance between protection and mobility.\n- **Weapon Choice:** Consider using weapons that scale with Intelligence or Faith for additional damage, such as **The Pursuer\u2019s** for melee complement or **Sword of Stars** for hybrid damage.\n\n## **7. Sample Stat Allocation (Level 120)**\n\nHere\u2019s an example of how you might distribute your stats by level 120:\n\n- **Vigor:** 30\n- **Attunement:** 20\n- **Endurance:** 20\n- **Vitality:** 15\n- **Strength:** 12\n- **Dexterity:** 12\n- **Intelligence:** 40\n- **Faith:** 40\n- **Luck:** 7 (default starting value, can be ignored)\n\n*Adjust these based on your playstyle and specific needs in the game.*\n\n## **8. Final Thoughts**\n\nBuilding a Pyromancer in Dark Souls 3 offers a versatile playstyle combining powerful ranged attacks with the ability to inflict status ailments. By focusing on Intelligence and Faith, ensuring you have ample Attunement slots, and maintaining sufficient survivability through Vigor and Endurance, you'll create a formidable spellcaster capable of handling the challenges of Lothric.\n\nRemember to experiment with different spells and equipment to find the combination that best suits your preferred combat style. Good luck on your journey through **Dark Souls 3**!",
